) The rapid spread of coronavirus from the city of Wuhan to the rest of China and around the world has led to the lock down of Chinese cities, counties and villages.

In the face of the sudden epidemic, the once unquenchable desires of rising social status and becoming rich overnight were no longer important for some people. They realize that things like freedom of speech and other truth that they had been indifferent towards are now as important as their lives.

Given this situation, people generally feel anxious and frail, and desperate for help. At the same time, the cruelty and inhumanity of the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) are on full display amidst this disaster. People feel disappointed and hopeless.

It’s now even more important for us, Falun Dafa practitioners, to care about people with our compassion, clarify the facts to them, and save them.

When I call China and tell people about Falun Dafa in recent days, the connection rate is higher than in the past, especially among higher ranking officials. Many are willing to listen now. The following is a part of my conversation with the mayor of a mid-size city in China.

After initial greetings, I said, “The coronavirus has spread wide, and many healthcare workers are infected as well. But do not despair. I have good news for you. There is a cure for the plague. It is the words, ‘Falun Dafa is good, Truthfulness-Compassion-Forbearance is good.’ When your heart is sincere, reciting these words can save you.”

I continued, “This plague had been foretold by the first minister of the Ming Dynasty, Liu Bowen. He wrote in his poem ‘If you ask when the plague will come, I would say about winter time, around September and October.’ The first documented case of someone with the Wuhan coronavirus occurred on December 1, 2019. Given the 14-day incubation period, the person was likely to have been infected in late November, which was October in the Chinese Lunar Calendar.

“Liu also predicted that ‘One worries about the onset of disaster in Huguang, which then spreads to all provinces across China.’ As you know, Huguang is a region that includes Hubei.”
